Let's roll out. Up and at 'em.

99
00:09:11.802 --> 00:09:14.179
Let's go. ladies. You know the drill.

100
00:09:23.981 --> 00:09:25.440
Thank you. Leanne.

101
00:10:13.739 --> 00:10:17.450
<i>The city Dev Ayesa
plans to build on Mars is called Meru.</i>

102
00:10:17.451 --> 00:10:19.619
<i>The city will include
living and working space</i>

103
00:10:19.620 --> 00:10:21.913
<i>for up to one million citizens.</i>

104
00:10:21.914 --> 00:10:25.875
<i>and use the resources of Mars
to be 100 percent sustainable</i>

105
00:10:25.876 --> 00:10:27.126
<i>and self-sufficient.</i>

106
00:10:27.127 --> 00:10:30.922
<i>Ayesa says Helios will begin
breaking ground within the year.</i>

107
00:10:30.923 --> 00:10:32.840
<i>Meru will not just be another base.</i>

108
00:10:32.841 --> 00:10:35.426
{\an8}<i>It won't be made up
of crew quarters or hab modules.</i>

109
00:10:35.427 --> 00:10:38.846
{\an8}<i>but homes where families can join
in converting the Red Planet</i>

110
00:10:38.847 --> 00:10:40.891
{\an8}<i>from a desert to a garden.</i>

111
00:10:41.475 --> 00:10:45.228
<i>And I mean that literally. In addition
to ample residential green space…</i>

112
00:10:45.229 --> 00:10:46.355
Liam!

113
00:10:47.105 --> 00:10:49.066
- Good morning.
- Where the fuck is Gene?

114
00:10:49.608 --> 00:10:53.111
I'm not entirely sure.
Maybe the Europa meeting?

115
00:10:54.947 --> 00:10:56.572
A few things. ma'am.

116
00:10:56.573 --> 00:11:00.284
The intelligence team needs some guidance
on those biosensor selectivity issues.

117
00:11:00.285 --> 00:11:01.702
Didn't I already respond to that?

118
00:11:01.703 --> 00:11:02.787
No.

119
00:11:02.788 --> 00:11:05.122
Well. UV shouldn't penetrate
more than an inch below the surface.

120
00:11:05.123 --> 00:11:07.124
So they need to redesign
the sensor to those specs.

121
00:11:07.125 --> 00:11:08.292
Yes. ma'am. I also wanted--

122
00:11:08.293 --> 00:11:10.837
Boss. the M-6 wants you
to come to Berlin next week.

123
00:11:10.838 --> 00:11:12.839
They're still not happy
with rate of refined iridium

124
00:11:12.840 --> 00:11:15.007
- being shipped back to Earth.
- They're never happy.

125
00:11:15.008 --> 00:11:16.009
Yeah.

126
00:11:16.927 --> 00:11:18.010
What the fuck. Gene?

127
00:11:18.011 --> 00:11:20.304
We didn't know he was
gonna do the interview.

128
00:11:20.305 --> 00:11:22.265
Isn't it your job to know?

129
00:11:22.266 --> 00:11:25.059
How the fuck does Dev make an
announcement like that without clearance?

130
00:11:25.060 --> 00:11:26.894
I know I sure as shit
didn't sign off on it.

131
00:11:26.895 --> 00:11:29.438
Look. everybody up there.
they're all Dev people.

132
00:11:29.439 --> 00:11:32.108
- He does whatever the hell he wants.
- That's not how this works.

133
00:11:32.109 --> 00:11:33.359
This is a public company.

134
00:11:33.360 --> 00:11:37.738
so you need to remind Dev that the
funding for his "city" is not approved.

135
00:11:37.739 --> 00:11:39.657
- He's not gonna be happy about that.
- Good.

136
00:11:39.658 --> 00:11:41.618
Not now. Sharon.

137
00:11:55.215 --> 00:11:56.258
Morning.

138
00:11:59.386 --> 00:12:00.928
Big day today.

139
00:12:00.929 --> 00:12:03.891
Yeah. can you believe it?
Our little girl. Gee.

140
00:12:07.728 --> 00:12:09.605
Sweetie? You up?

141
00:12:20.032 --> 00:12:21.033
Sweetie?

142
00:12:24.578 --> 00:12:26.330
No. she must have got up early.

143
00:12:27.331 --> 00:12:29.040
Come on. I better get dressed.

144
00:12:29.041 --> 00:12:31.083
Or we could get undressed?

145
00:12:31.084 --> 00:12:35.087
Baby. No. Come on. You know
we got a lot to do before the ceremony.

146
00:12:35.088 --> 00:12:36.089
I'll be so quick.

147
00:12:36.757 --> 00:12:37.925
How romantic.

148
00:12:39.718 --> 00:12:40.801
Okay.

149
00:12:40.802 --> 00:12:42.763
- Okay. okay. Okay. okay.
- Quick?

150
00:13:55.669 --> 00:13:57.838
- Looking sharp. Admiral.
- Damn right.

151
00:14:07.639 --> 00:14:09.892
Contact. All reading nominal.

152
00:14:28.827 --> 00:14:31.371
Goddamn it. Ed. We're working here.

153
00:14:34.458 --> 00:14:35.959
Sons of bitches.

154
00:14:38.504 --> 00:14:40.505
Told you we didn't have time.

155
00:14:40.506 --> 00:14:41.882
Yeah. but it was still worth it.

156
00:14:48.555 --> 00:14:50.724
Man. I wish they would stop doing that.

157
00:14:51.725 --> 00:14:54.353
- Sure you do.
- I do.

158
00:15:15.415 --> 00:15:17.209
Oh. good morning.

159
00:15:17.793 --> 00:15:20.837
Good morning. You guys coming later?

160
00:15:20.838 --> 00:15:22.464
Yes. of course.

161
00:15:22.965 --> 00:15:24.841
We already prepared gift.

162
00:15:24.842 --> 00:15:25.926
Yeah.

163
00:15:30.472 --> 00:15:31.764
Then show me your permit.

164
00:15:31.765 --> 00:15:34.433
Permit? This is barely a railing.

165
00:15:34.434 --> 00:15:36.811
Unauthorized additions
to property are strictly forbidden.

166
00:15:36.812 --> 00:15:37.895
It's a safety issue.

167
00:15:37.896 --> 00:15:40.481
These are pressurized modules.
If everyone's making their own mods…

168
00:15:40.482 --> 00:15:44.485
Safety. come on.
This makes it more safe for people.

169
00:15:44.486 --> 00:15:45.945
Try it.

170
00:15:45.946 --> 00:15:47.113
Take it down.

171
00:15:47.114 --> 00:15:48.115
Have a nice sol.

172
00:15:49.449 --> 00:15:51.784
I told you not to put this thing up.

173
00:15:51.785 --> 00:15:55.663
Same old bullshit. They make
those rules just to show who is boss.

174
00:15:55.664 --> 00:15:58.499
Yeah. well. now we owe
the boss another 300 bucks.

175
00:15:58.500 --> 00:16:00.334
Did you get the trays
for the ceremony ready?

176
00:16:00.335 --> 00:16:01.419
- We're running late.
- Yes. Yes.

177
00:16:01.420 --> 00:16:03.087
- Please. come on.
- Okay.

178
00:16:03.088 --> 00:16:04.089
Right there.

179
00:16:09.261 --> 00:16:10.636
Beautiful. Ilya.

180
00:16:10.637 --> 00:16:11.972
Anything for our girl.

181
00:16:12.556 --> 00:16:14.474
Tendi made it all with love.

182
00:16:15.475 --> 00:16:18.519
- Try one?
- I wish I could. but we are late.

183
00:16:18.520 --> 00:16:20.522
- Oh. okay.
- Can you carry a box?

184
00:16:21.982 --> 00:16:24.400
- You got it? Are you sure?
- Yeah. I got it.

185
00:16:24.401 --> 00:16:26.320
- Just trying to be nice.
- Oh. man.

186
00:17:07.027 --> 00:17:09.112
<i>Korolev Outpost One. Baldwin.</i>

187
00:17:09.780 --> 00:17:13.242
<i>Retrieving sample 7B from drill site 895.</i>

188
00:17:14.535 --> 00:17:16.244
<i>Coring tube is intact.</i>

189
00:17:17.329 --> 00:17:19.164
<i>Proceeding to sample 7C.</i>

190
00:17:19.998 --> 00:17:21.250
<i>Copy that. Kelly.</i>

191
00:17:22.542 --> 00:17:23.752
<i>Hey. Sabir?</i>

192
00:17:24.545 --> 00:17:27.630
<i>Did you get the mass spec readings
for region five.</i>

193
00:17:27.631 --> 00:17:29.632
<i>drill site 894 yet?</i>

194
00:17:29.633 --> 00:17:33.719
<i>Here they are.
Preliminary sample analysis…</i>

195
00:17:33.720 --> 00:17:35.305
<i>Negative for organic compounds.</i>

196
00:17:37.891 --> 00:17:39.977
Fourth fucking negative this month.

197
00:17:40.519 --> 00:17:43.271
<i>Oh. Kel. you may want to cut
your EVA a little short today.</i>

198
00:17:43.272 --> 00:17:46.357
<i>You've got your son's shindig.
And it's already 10 o'clock.</i>

199
00:17:46.358 --> 00:17:48.317
Shit. Thanks. Sabir.

200
00:17:48.318 --> 00:17:51.028
<i>You're gonna need to
haul ass to get there in time.</i>

201
00:17:51.029 --> 00:17:52.030
Copy.

202
00:17:53.532 --> 00:17:56.367
Get the hopper fueled
and ready for preflight checks.

203
00:17:56.368 --> 00:17:57.369
<i>Copy that.</i>

204
00:17:58.662 --> 00:18:01.290
A tree begins with one seed.

205
00:18:01.874 --> 00:18:03.709
and slowly it begins to grow.

206
00:18:04.543 --> 00:18:06.919
Leaves sprout. flowers will bloom.

207
00:18:06.920 --> 00:18:11.049
{\an8}And those flowers will turn
into the fruit of that tree.

208
00:18:12.426 --> 00:18:16.138
That same fruit contains in itself
the seeds for the next tree

209
00:18:16.638 --> 00:18:18.723
and the next and the next.

210
00:18:18.724 --> 00:18:20.976
And like that. the forest grows.

211
00:18:22.769 --> 00:18:26.272
And as I think about the young people
here today. I'm reminded of

212
00:18:26.273 --> 00:18:29.859
one of my favorite fairy tales
about a Russian czar.

213
00:18:29.860 --> 00:18:31.944
He was very. very old.
He could barely stand.

214
00:18:31.945 --> 00:18:35.823
- but he heard there was a special tree…
- Jesus. Kel. It started ten minutes ago.

215
00:18:35.824 --> 00:18:36.825
I know.

216
00:18:37.826 --> 00:18:39.702
- You didn't miss much.
- …that had golden apples.

217
00:18:39.703 --> 00:18:43.373
And if one was to take a bite of that
magical fruit. he would turn young again.

218
00:18:44.041 --> 00:18:47.251
So he sent his three sons off
to find those apples

219
00:18:47.252 --> 00:18:49.378
and bring those apples to him.

220
00:18:49.379 --> 00:18:52.507
Now. remember.
this is a Russian fairy tale

221
00:18:52.508 --> 00:18:56.552
so of course there is a lot of death
and misery between and along the way

222
00:18:56.553 --> 00:18:58.846
which I'm gonna skip here. but at the end.

223
00:18:58.847 --> 00:19:05.436
the czar realizes that the true
apples of youth are his children.

224
00:19:05.437 --> 00:19:07.730
They are the future.

225
00:19:07.731 --> 00:19:12.235
And I could not be more proud to be
standing here as your governor today.

226
00:19:12.236 --> 00:19:15.030
Yeah. governor of bullshit.

227
00:19:15.572 --> 00:19:19.075
I mean. nothing's sacred anymore.
Man. look at these woodpeckers.

228
00:19:19.076 --> 00:19:20.993
What the hell do they think
we're gonna do?

229
00:19:20.994 --> 00:19:22.078
Dad. Not now.

230
00:19:22.079 --> 00:19:26.667
So. in the Russian tradition.
as I ring the school bell one last time…

231
00:19:29.753 --> 00:19:34.633
I present to you this year's graduates
of Happy Valley Institute of Education.

232
00:19:40.264 --> 00:19:42.015
Lilith Beatrice Dale.

233
00:19:44.810 --> 00:19:48.939
Lily will be joining her older sister
at Tulane where she will study journalism.

234
00:19:49.731 --> 00:19:51.066
Congratulations.

235
00:19:53.151 --> 00:19:54.862
Marcus James Haskell.

236
00:19:55.612 --> 00:19:57.697
Marcus has joined
the United States Marine Corps.

237
00:19:57.698 --> 00:19:58.740
Oorah!

238
00:19:59.825 --> 00:20:00.992
Congratulations.

239
00:20:00.993 --> 00:20:02.828
Gulsora Akilmatova.

240
00:20:03.662 --> 00:20:07.457
She's enrolled at the Institute of Cairo.
Film Studies.

241
00:20:08.917 --> 00:20:10.711
A Tarkovsky I see. huh?

242
00:20:16.258 --> 00:20:19.887
And finally. Alex Poletov Baldwin.

243
00:20:24.766 --> 00:20:26.976
- Go. Alex!
- Yeah! Alex!

244
00:20:26.977 --> 00:20:29.104
Alex will be staying here on Mars with us.

245
00:20:29.897 --> 00:20:32.733
And I'm sure he will have
grand things ahead of him.

246
00:20:36.653 --> 00:20:38.363
Alex. congratulations.

247
00:20:41.116 --> 00:20:43.492
To all the graduates I say…

248
00:20:43.493 --> 00:20:44.494
Congratulations.

249
00:20:53.504 --> 00:20:55.338
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

250
00:20:55.339 --> 00:20:58.257
We are so proud of you and Marcus.

251
00:20:58.258 --> 00:21:02.471
So what's next for you?
I'm guessing biology like your mom?

252
00:21:03.263 --> 00:21:05.348
- I was gonna maybe…
- No. come work the asteroid. kid.

253
00:21:05.349 --> 00:21:09.186
- Yeah. Dad.
- Zero G. triple OT. Nothing better.

254
00:21:10.062 --> 00:21:11.104
I…

255
00:21:12.481 --> 00:21:14.398
I'm still weighing my options. Yeah.

256
00:21:14.399 --> 00:21:18.195
Yeah. and this summer. she'll be
interning at the NNC outlet up here.

257
00:21:19.488 --> 00:21:22.240
You should try and get a job
at <i>The New Yorker</i> after college.

258
00:21:22.241 --> 00:21:23.575
I just love their cartoons.

259
00:21:24.326 --> 00:21:25.660
Well. we're all mighty proud of her.

260
00:21:25.661 --> 00:21:28.247
And Lily and her sister.
they're the first Dales to go to college.

261
00:21:29.706 --> 00:21:31.958
And you two. Empty-nesters. huh?

262
00:21:31.959 --> 00:21:35.211
Like newlyweds all over again.
You know what I mean?

263
00:21:35.212 --> 00:21:36.630
Unfortunately I do.

264
00:21:38.632 --> 00:21:39.800
I'm done.

265
00:21:40.843 --> 00:21:44.470
How could you embarrass us
like that with Governor Polivanov?

266
00:21:44.471 --> 00:21:47.348
You know your father needs this job.

267
00:21:47.349 --> 00:21:48.516
Mom. stop.

268
00:21:48.517 --> 00:21:51.728
Take it all in. Take it all in.

269
00:21:52.604 --> 00:21:55.774
Everything that's happened
led to this moment.

270
00:21:57.192 --> 00:22:01.029
You know. you're gonna do things that
people in this room can't even fathom.

271
00:22:03.699 --> 00:22:05.284
It's on you to make the next move.

272
00:22:06.326 --> 00:22:07.411
You're a man now.

273
00:22:07.911 --> 00:22:09.370
You know. that's why
I want you to come down

274
00:22:09.371 --> 00:22:11.372
- to the next SDM meeting at Ilya's.
- Alex.

275
00:22:11.373 --> 00:22:14.501
You should have a voice in shaping
the future up here. you know.

276
00:22:15.169 --> 00:22:16.586
- Yeah?
- Yes.

277
00:22:16.587 --> 00:22:17.837
- You up for it?
- Sure.

278
00:22:17.838 --> 00:22:20.298
Yeah. Yeah. I just…
I better go check on Mom.

279
00:22:20.299 --> 00:22:21.465
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

280
00:22:21.466 --> 00:22:22.467
All right.

281
00:22:34.855 --> 00:22:35.898
Jesus. that was awful.

282
00:22:36.398 --> 00:22:37.566
Not as bad as that party.

283
00:22:38.483 --> 00:22:39.942
Pure torture.

284
00:22:39.943 --> 00:22:42.486
My grandpa would not stop
telling me I'm a man now.

285
00:22:42.487 --> 00:22:43.739
Yeah. you're not even close.

286
00:22:45.115 --> 00:22:46.116
Thanks.

287
00:22:46.617 --> 00:22:49.243
You know you have
the coolest grandpa in the world. right?

288
00:22:49.244 --> 00:22:50.453
Grows the best shit.

289
00:22:50.454 --> 00:22:52.955
I still don't understand
how they let you into the Marines.

290
00:22:52.956 --> 00:22:54.499
Oh. well. they clearly
lowered their standards.

291
00:22:56.752 --> 00:22:58.921
- You're just jealous.
- Of you?

292
00:22:59.588 --> 00:23:01.005
No. I don't think so.

293
00:23:01.006 --> 00:23:03.758
Oh. the fact that I can
actually leave this shithole?

294
00:23:03.759 --> 00:23:06.219
Hey. Don't call it that. This is our home.

295
00:23:06.220 --> 00:23:08.137
You're leaving too. Miss Tulane.

296
00:23:08.138 --> 00:23:09.472
Not until the end of summer.

297
00:23:09.473 --> 00:23:12.266
And for the millionth time.
I'm not going for good.

298
00:23:12.267 --> 00:23:13.518
It's just until I get my degree.

299
00:23:13.519 --> 00:23:15.102
Yeah. well. your sister said
the same thing.

300
00:23:15.103 --> 00:23:17.188
I'm not my sister.
Why would you bring up my sister?

301
00:23:17.189 --> 00:23:19.398
- You're kinda acting like her right now.
- What does that even…

302
00:23:19.399 --> 00:23:22.026
- What does that have to do with anything?
- All right. All right. all right.

303
00:23:22.027 --> 00:23:24.904
- No fighting tonight. please.
- Oh. my God.

304
00:23:24.905 --> 00:23:26.031
Please.

305
00:23:26.990 --> 00:23:27.991
Thank you.

306
00:23:28.992 --> 00:23:29.993
Okay…

307
00:23:31.870 --> 00:23:33.622
What are we toasting to? Yeah?

308
00:23:34.122 --> 00:23:35.958
Please don't say. "Our futures."

309
00:23:37.251 --> 00:23:38.877
- To Mars.
- Oh. God. No.

310
00:23:44.883 --> 00:23:45.884
To…

311
00:23:47.177 --> 00:23:49.137
To friends.

312
00:23:50.597 --> 00:23:53.851
Come on. Come on. To friends forever.

313
00:23:55.435 --> 00:23:57.938
- What? Dude.
- Well. I'm sorry. That's pretty corny.

314
00:23:58.480 --> 00:24:00.649
- All right. fine. Give me the cup.
- Yeah.

315
00:24:04.611 --> 00:24:05.612
To friends.

316
00:24:09.658 --> 00:24:11.033
To friends.

317
00:24:11.034 --> 00:24:12.451
- Cheers.
- With benefits.

318
00:24:12.452 --> 00:24:13.745
Okay.

319
00:24:25.632 --> 00:24:27.592
Looks like the board's not gonna
approve the overage

320
00:24:27.593 --> 00:24:28.927
for the Europa drill redesign.

321
00:24:29.845 --> 00:24:32.306
They say they already approved
70 million last month.

322
00:24:35.893 --> 00:24:38.394
So it's our fault the ice shell
covering Europa's ocean

323
00:24:38.395 --> 00:24:39.604
is thicker than we estimated?

324
00:24:39.605 --> 00:24:42.190
I think Dev's announcement today
is making them nervous.

325
00:24:42.191 --> 00:24:45.444
I mean. who knows how much money he's
trying to grab for that <i>SimCity</i> of his.

326
00:24:46.612 --> 00:24:48.696
They're all terrified
of telling him. "No."

327
00:24:48.697 --> 00:24:51.533
And in the meantime. we have
our hands tied behind our backs. I mean…

328
00:24:55.245 --> 00:24:57.580
Walt's team just successfully landed

329
00:24:57.581 --> 00:24:59.832
another group of SEEKER-12s on Titan.

330
00:24:59.833 --> 00:25:03.419
This is one of the most promising places
to find life in the solar system.

331
00:25:03.420 --> 00:25:06.088
but if we don't keep
funding these missions.

332
00:25:06.089 --> 00:25:07.925
Kuragin's going to find life before we do.

333
00:25:09.801 --> 00:25:12.303
Well. we could always take
more funding from Korolev.

334
00:25:12.304 --> 00:25:13.305
No.

335
00:25:14.306 --> 00:25:17.725
Mars still holds some promise.
Korolev Crater--

336
00:25:17.726 --> 00:25:20.562
Has turned up nothing in the last decade.

337
00:25:23.649 --> 00:25:26.527
- I know she's your friend.
- That's got nothing to do with it.

338
00:25:29.696 --> 00:25:31.865
Well. if we want more money
for these other missions.

339
00:25:33.325 --> 00:25:34.743
we're gonna have to find it somewhere.

340
00:26:14.950 --> 00:26:15.951
Alex?

341
00:26:17.661 --> 00:26:18.829
Alex?

342
00:26:21.832 --> 00:26:23.792
I'm launching back up to Korolev
in a few hours.

343
00:26:25.043 --> 00:26:26.169
You just got back.

344
00:26:26.170 --> 00:26:30.048
I know. I'm sorry. but I had to cut my EVA
short to be here in time for your big day.

345
00:26:31.633 --> 00:26:33.427
You probably should have
stayed up there then. huh?

346
00:26:34.469 --> 00:26:35.470
Hey.

347
00:26:37.306 --> 00:26:40.017
You know I would never
miss something like that.

348
00:26:41.810 --> 00:26:44.730
I… I know. Mom.
I was just messing with you.

349
00:26:45.314 --> 00:26:48.859
Okay. Well. it's hard to tell sometimes.

350
00:26:52.613 --> 00:26:53.822
I'm gonna pack.

351
00:26:54.489 --> 00:26:58.326
Have you seen my VR3 anywhere?
I can't seem to find it.

352
00:26:58.327 --> 00:26:59.869
No. Haven't seen it.

353
00:26:59.870 --> 00:27:02.831
Okay. well.
Guess I'll just use Sabir's again.

354
00:27:05.250 --> 00:27:08.170
By the way. are you going
to that SDM meeting with Poppy?

355
00:27:08.670 --> 00:27:09.755
Yeah. maybe.

356
00:27:20.599 --> 00:27:21.683
Hey.

357
00:27:29.066 --> 00:27:31.568
I know this is a lot.

358
00:27:32.528 --> 00:27:35.571
Right? Feeling like you need to figure out

359
00:27:35.572 --> 00:27:37.699
what you're gonna do
for the rest of your life.

360
00:27:40.202 --> 00:27:43.539
But you really only need to figure out
what you're gonna do next.

361
00:27:47.000 --> 00:27:48.460
- All right?
- Yeah.

362
00:27:51.922 --> 00:27:52.965
Probably a nap.

363
00:27:54.424 --> 00:27:55.592
Sounds good.

364
00:27:58.262 --> 00:28:01.139
Oh. and this came for you.

365
00:28:14.403 --> 00:28:16.989
<i>Cabrón</i>. we gotta take control
of our own lives. man.

366
00:28:18.615 --> 00:28:21.158
- That's not what I said.
- But that's what it sounds like.

367
00:28:21.159 --> 00:28:23.786
He means we need someone
from Mars on the M-6.

368
00:28:23.787 --> 00:28:24.954
Someone we pick.

369
00:28:24.955 --> 00:28:26.747
But that's what it says right here.

370
00:28:26.748 --> 00:28:28.959
It's how you're wording it.
It's confusing.

371
00:28:29.543 --> 00:28:31.794
Okay. Well. then I have
a really good idea.

372
00:28:31.795 --> 00:28:33.297
Next time. you write the petition.

373
00:28:34.047 --> 00:28:37.300
Maybe the reason the M-6 hasn't
responded to our last five petitions

374
00:28:37.301 --> 00:28:39.635
is 'cause they don't understand
what the hell we're even asking for.

375
00:28:39.636 --> 00:28:41.846
They haven't responded
'cause all they give a shit about

376
00:28:41.847 --> 00:28:43.514
is how much iridium
we ship them every week.

377
00:28:43.515 --> 00:28:46.893
Yeah. They're never gonna let us
actually control our destiny.

378
00:28:46.894 --> 00:28:47.977
Not till we make 'em.

379
00:28:47.978 --> 00:28:51.397
By doing what? Spray-painting
"Free Mars" on a few walls?

380
00:28:51.398 --> 00:28:53.566
Well. at least whoever's doing that's
got some guts.

381
00:28:53.567 --> 00:28:55.194
We could use some more of that up here.

382
00:28:55.944 --> 00:29:00.323
I mean. we need to start doing more
than just sending pieces of paper to Earth

383
00:29:00.324 --> 00:29:01.866
with a few signatures on them.

384
00:29:01.867 --> 00:29:03.159
I get it. guys. I do.

385
00:29:03.160 --> 00:29:05.661
Nobody here is happy
with the way things turned out.

386
00:29:05.662 --> 00:29:07.788
Like constantly
looking over your shoulder.

387
00:29:07.789 --> 00:29:11.125
worried that they'll send you or
your family back if you step out of line.

388
00:29:11.126 --> 00:29:13.586
Look. we all want a say in our future.

389
00:29:13.587 --> 00:29:15.464
But we can't fall back into chaos.

390
00:29:16.423 --> 00:29:20.676
I know it's not the sexy way. but this is
how change happens. Inch by inch.

391
00:29:20.677 --> 00:29:24.515
Change happens when a few
determined individuals make it happen.

392
00:29:25.307 --> 00:29:27.099
You forget how old Goldilocks
wound up here?

393
00:29:27.100 --> 00:29:29.894
No. Ed. I have not forgotten.
I have also not forgotten

394
00:29:29.895 --> 00:29:32.271
that Sam Massey is still rotting away
in a federal prison.

395
00:29:32.272 --> 00:29:33.856
Oh. she knew what she was getting into.

396
00:29:33.857 --> 00:29:36.776
- Let's not let her sacrifice be in vain.
- She did it for all of us.

397
00:29:36.777 --> 00:29:38.319
I agree. That's what I'm saying.

398
00:29:38.320 --> 00:29:40.780
All right. All right. all right…

399
00:29:40.781 --> 00:29:42.573
Look. it's getting close
to the lunch rush.

400
00:29:42.574 --> 00:29:45.952
So. for now. this meeting of the SDM
is hereby adjourned.

401
00:29:45.953 --> 00:29:48.287
All right. You all heard the lady.

402
00:29:48.288 --> 00:29:49.289
Till next week.

403
00:30:05.556 --> 00:30:07.015
Some trouble on the home front?

404
00:30:09.560 --> 00:30:10.561
How you know?

405
00:30:11.436 --> 00:30:12.437
I've been there.

406
00:30:19.403 --> 00:30:22.114
Whoa. Easy on the sauce there.
my dumpling.

407
00:30:29.913 --> 00:30:30.956
What's going on?

408
00:30:35.752 --> 00:30:37.045
Moon Yeong…

409
00:30:39.590 --> 00:30:40.799
She…

410
00:30:42.134 --> 00:30:45.596
She has a friend from Pyongyang.

411
00:30:47.681 --> 00:30:48.682
A man.

412
00:30:50.684 --> 00:30:52.727
And she know this guy from Pyongyang?

413
00:30:52.728 --> 00:30:55.688
No. He come here same as her.
in cargo crate.

414
00:30:55.689 --> 00:30:57.065
Oh. he's a Crater. huh?

415
00:30:58.192 --> 00:31:00.569
And they used to work together
at her other job.

416
00:31:01.069 --> 00:31:03.488
I tell her.
"I do not like you working there.

417
00:31:04.031 --> 00:31:06.282
and I can provide for our family."

418
00:31:06.283 --> 00:31:09.660
Yeah. see. they tend to not like it
when you say that to 'em.

419
00:31:09.661 --> 00:31:11.412
You know. she's a modern woman now.

420
00:31:11.413 --> 00:31:14.415
No. she did not use
to speak to me that way.

421
00:31:14.416 --> 00:31:16.250
Yeah. well. what the hell
you think was gonna happen

422
00:31:16.251 --> 00:31:17.544
when you brought her up here?

423
00:31:20.589 --> 00:31:23.382
Listen. I've been married three times.

424
00:31:23.383 --> 00:31:25.886
and if there's one thing I've learned…

425
00:31:27.554 --> 00:31:30.516
it's that I haven't learned shit.

426
00:31:35.270 --> 00:31:36.897
You're fucked.

427
00:31:39.024 --> 00:31:40.317
Hey. Lily…

428
00:31:41.568 --> 00:31:42.986
You seen Alex around here?

429
00:31:44.363 --> 00:31:46.364
Not since yesterday. no. Why?

430
00:31:46.365 --> 00:31:49.910
He promised he was going to
join me at the meeting.

431
00:31:50.494 --> 00:31:51.537
Little shithead.

432
00:33:29.760 --> 00:33:32.178
Come on. If you guys take me in.
they'll send me Earthside.

433
00:33:32.179 --> 00:33:34.388
You should've thought of that
before you tried to steal O2.

434
00:33:34.389 --> 00:33:35.973
<i>Dispatch. all units.</i>

435
00:33:35.974 --> 00:33:38.684
<i>Looks like we've got another
suicide out past the big dig.</i>

436
00:33:38.685 --> 00:33:42.396
<i>Any available hopper pilot. we need
to get an investigator out there ASAP.</i>

437
00:33:42.397 --> 00:33:45.066
Hey. can you process him?
I got to get all the stick time I can.

438
00:33:45.067 --> 00:33:46.526
- Yeah. I got you.
- Thanks. Fred.

439
00:33:46.527 --> 00:33:48.487
Copy. Dispatch. Boyd. I'm on it.

440
00:33:49.905 --> 00:33:51.614
<i>Control. Boyd.</i>

441
00:33:51.615 --> 00:33:54.325
<i>Down at 45 meters. AGL.</i>

442
00:33:54.326 --> 00:33:56.494
<i>Beginning manual descent.</i>

443
00:33:56.495 --> 00:33:59.163
<i>Boyd. control.
We show you on approach for landing</i>

444
00:33:59.164 --> 00:34:02.501
{\an8}- <i>at grid 3-0-6-9.</i>
- Flight control. Boyd.

445
00:34:03.085 --> 00:34:05.921
{\an8}LZ in sight. Request landing clearance.

446
00:34:06.713 --> 00:34:09.757
{\an8}<i>Boyd. control. You're clear to land</i>.

447
00:34:20.393 --> 00:34:24.188
Oh. fuck me.
You never get used to seeing this shit.

448
00:34:25.607 --> 00:34:26.983
Who found the body again?

449
00:34:26.984 --> 00:34:29.945
The Baldwin kid.
Sounds like he's pretty shaken up.

450
00:34:30.654 --> 00:34:31.864
I bet.

451
00:34:34.867 --> 00:34:38.536
Dispatch. looks like another sad bastard
decided to pull a Gordo.

452
00:34:39.329 --> 00:34:41.372
- A what?
- <i>Copy that.</i>

453
00:34:41.373 --> 00:34:44.709
We've had several suicides
like this over the years.

454
00:34:44.710 --> 00:34:48.505
It's a surface run.
See how far you can get without a suit.

455
00:34:55.971 --> 00:34:57.638
It does seem like a long distance

456
00:34:57.639 --> 00:34:59.683
to land from the rover
all the way over here.

457
00:35:00.434 --> 00:35:03.936
No. you gotta remember.
Mars has a third of the gravity of Earth.

458
00:35:03.937 --> 00:35:05.521
So they get a lot farther that way.

459
00:35:05.522 --> 00:35:07.940
Yeah. I'm familiar
with how gravity works. but--

460
00:35:07.941 --> 00:35:10.235
Come on. let's get
the body onto the hopper.

461
00:35:17.618 --> 00:35:20.536
Body shows signs consistent
with rapid depressurization

462
00:35:20.537 --> 00:35:22.872
and exposure to the Martian environment.

463
00:35:22.873 --> 00:35:26.667
Epidermis exhibits significant dehydration
due to vacuum exposure

464
00:35:26.668 --> 00:35:29.670
and severe bloating
from internal body pressure.

465
00:35:29.671 --> 00:35:31.756
All right. what do we got. kids?

466
00:35:31.757 --> 00:35:34.091
Looks like another Crater
killed himself. Sheriff.

467
00:35:34.092 --> 00:35:37.012
Name's Yoon Tae-Min.
Claimed asylum from North Korea last year.

468
00:35:38.388 --> 00:35:39.805
Where did you get that?

469
00:35:39.806 --> 00:35:42.643
Social Services takes photos of 'em
if they apply for assistance.

470
00:35:43.727 --> 00:35:44.811
Thanks. Boyd.

471
