00:52:03.874 --> 00:52:05.124
He put up with a lot.

712
00:52:05.125 --> 00:52:06.668
He was a wonderful man.

713
00:52:07.252 --> 00:52:09.963
He would've been so proud
if he could see you now.

714
00:52:12.174 --> 00:52:13.342
I don't know.

715
00:52:15.677 --> 00:52:18.388
I think he would want to
see me happy. And…

716
00:52:21.683 --> 00:52:23.352
I don't know if I am.

717
00:52:26.522 --> 00:52:30.067
Don't get me wrong.
I'm so grateful. It's just…

718
00:52:33.362 --> 00:52:35.948
You have this idea
of what you think you want.

719
00:52:37.866 --> 00:52:39.534
and then you get it. and…

720
00:52:39.535 --> 00:52:40.786
It nearly kills you.

721
00:52:48.043 --> 00:52:49.545
You know. Aleida.

722
00:52:51.380 --> 00:52:54.299
it might be hard to see it right now.

723
00:52:55.926 --> 00:52:56.927
but you're doing okay.

724
00:52:57.678 --> 00:53:00.013
- I'm not.
- Better than I ever did.

725
00:53:00.639 --> 00:53:04.977
You got Victor. your kids. your work.

726
00:53:05.769 --> 00:53:10.482
And I'm sure it's hard to
balance it all sometimes. but…

727
00:53:12.693 --> 00:53:15.028
at least you have something to balance.

728
00:53:16.446 --> 00:53:19.198
I mean. I spent my whole life working.

729
00:53:19.199 --> 00:53:21.951
pushing for more. keeping everyone away.

730
00:53:21.952 --> 00:53:23.203
And in the end…

731
00:53:35.215 --> 00:53:36.717
here I am.

732
00:53:45.100 --> 00:53:46.268
I'm still here.

733
00:53:49.104 --> 00:53:52.357
And I'm grateful for that.

734
00:54:14.630 --> 00:54:16.923
I appreciate you. man.
That's really kind. Seriously.

735
00:54:16.924 --> 00:54:19.718
Hey. I'll see you again. right? Thank you.

736
00:54:25.307 --> 00:54:26.767
Okay.

737
00:54:31.772 --> 00:54:32.773
Dad?

738
00:54:35.526 --> 00:54:37.402
I was… I was thinking

739
00:54:38.278 --> 00:54:41.907
that maybe I should be part
of the next SDM meeting.

740
00:54:43.116 --> 00:54:44.201
No. No way.

741
00:54:45.869 --> 00:54:47.454
Well. Mr. Baldwin said Alex could.

742
00:54:47.955 --> 00:54:51.207
Well. that's their business. okay?

743
00:54:51.208 --> 00:54:53.376
I don't want you mixed up
in all that here.

744
00:54:53.377 --> 00:54:54.460
Why not?

745
00:54:54.461 --> 00:54:56.045
Because you're about to
go down to college.

746
00:54:56.046 --> 00:54:57.463
and that's what you should be focused on.

747
00:54:57.464 --> 00:54:59.424
Yeah. but I'm coming back here.

748
00:54:59.967 --> 00:55:02.845
This is where I'm from.
This is… This is who I am.

749
00:55:04.179 --> 00:55:06.723
And I wanna help change things
for the better.

750
00:55:07.850 --> 00:55:09.768
- Like you did.
- Well. I mean…

751
00:55:10.978 --> 00:55:13.479
that was different. And that was. it was…

752
00:55:13.480 --> 00:55:15.648
- It was badass is what it was.
- Well…

753
00:55:15.649 --> 00:55:18.025
Do you see how people look up to you here?

754
00:55:18.026 --> 00:55:19.027
It…

755
00:55:19.695 --> 00:55:23.699
I don't know. It makes me
wanna help in any way I can.

756
00:55:27.995 --> 00:55:29.579
Well. let me think about it. okay?

757
00:55:29.580 --> 00:55:33.041
It was not even railing.
It was just a little…

758
00:55:34.501 --> 00:55:37.128
- You understand?
- I'm gonna rescue Boyd from Ilya.

759
00:55:37.129 --> 00:55:40.423
Will you talk some sense
to them. Celia? Please.

760
00:55:40.424 --> 00:55:42.300
There is free drinks in it for you.

761
00:55:42.301 --> 00:55:44.385
I'm pretty sure you don't want to be
offering me a bribe. Ilya.

762
00:55:44.386 --> 00:55:46.596
- No. he's not…
- We were just trying to help each other.

763
00:55:46.597 --> 00:55:47.763
What's wrong with that?

764
00:55:47.764 --> 00:55:50.683
You're our customer.
You come here so much.

765
00:55:50.684 --> 00:55:52.393
<i>Boyd. dispatch.</i>

766
00:55:52.394 --> 00:55:54.562
<i>Your presence has been requested
at Central.</i>

767
00:55:54.563 --> 00:55:56.023
We talked about this.

768
00:55:56.690 --> 00:55:58.233
Dispatch. Boyd. Copy.

769
00:55:59.526 --> 00:56:00.986
I gotta head out.

770
00:56:01.570 --> 00:56:03.404
- All right.
- Nice try. Ilya.

771
00:56:03.405 --> 00:56:05.115
- See ya again.
- Bye.

772
00:56:06.325 --> 00:56:10.328
- Brother. you can't bribe an officer.
- Maybe she can do something.

773
00:56:10.329 --> 00:56:11.538
Maybe she can put you in jail.

774
00:56:12.164 --> 00:56:13.247
Been there.

775
00:56:13.248 --> 00:56:15.333
I want this clean. I want this efficient.

776
00:56:15.334 --> 00:56:16.584
I want this by the book.

777
00:56:16.585 --> 00:56:18.377
In and out. nobody gets hurt.
Do you understand?

778
00:56:18.378 --> 00:56:19.421
Yes. sir.

779
00:56:20.797 --> 00:56:23.091
- You wanted to see me. sir?
- There she is.

780
00:56:23.675 --> 00:56:24.967
Is everything okay?

781
00:56:24.968 --> 00:56:27.136
We found DNA under the vic's fingernails.

782
00:56:27.137 --> 00:56:30.349
Thanks to your persistence.
we're about to arrest a suspect.

783
00:56:31.350 --> 00:56:34.810
We wouldn't be here without you.
Thought you'd like to join us.

784
00:56:34.811 --> 00:56:36.729
Yes. sir. Thank you. sir.

785
00:56:36.730 --> 00:56:38.065
All right. let's go.

786
00:56:38.565 --> 00:56:41.818
I want arrest protocol followed
to a tee. people.

787
00:56:42.319 --> 00:56:44.363
Gonna be a lotta eyeballs on this one.

788
00:56:48.867 --> 00:56:49.952
Who's the suspect?

789
00:57:00.295 --> 00:57:01.755
Lee Jung-Gil.

790
00:57:03.006 --> 00:57:04.215
Yes?

791
00:57:04.216 --> 00:57:06.802
You're under arrest
for the murder of Yoon Tae-min.

792
00:57:09.972 --> 00:57:11.056
Let's go.

793
00:57:12.305 --> 00:58:12.193
Do you want subtitles for any video?
